owing her athelfi would quickly see that the assassin had  left the group, Elektra wanted to find the stallion quick.  But, where?  And there it was...like an offering. The stallion standing silent in the woods.  A set of black reigns had it harnessed, and Elektra quickly grabbed it and led it back to camp.  <br>
<br>
She glanced to her athelfi and then walked over near the fire chanting to the Gods.  She grabbed a spear holding it near the chest of the stallion and then as her chanting rose, the assassin sent the spear plunging deep into it's heart.  The horse kicked and attempted to rear for a moment before it fell to the ground in a horrid animal scream.<br>
<br>
Elektra kneeled next to the gasping horse, and pulled out the spear.  Then as her chanting subsided, the assassin plunged her fist into the wound.  Gripping the heart, she twisted it in her fingers and pulled it out quickly.  Then held it high into the air, &quot;Gods of Olympus, grant us success and victory to overcome our enemy and retrieve our athelfi and vasilissa safely back to our arms.&quot;  Picking up a dagger she slit the heart, that poured it's contents over the assassin.  Then she rubbed it against her body marking her with the stallions blood. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solariwolf@amazonsunite>solariwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Themiscryian War Queen</span><br>  Posts: 186<br> <font color=#993300>(4/18/03 3:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=160>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: the vision</span><hr size=1> Solari had watched from the shadows of her shelter what Elektra had done. She knew who had ordered it as well. She felt a small fire burn in the pit of her stomach. Solari had never believed in making sacrifices to help in battle. She had good wits about her and enough luck to get her through. But now she wondered if Hera believed in her as her mother did. <br>
&quot;Hera, i know you are there listening.&quot; She said silently so not to disturb Marpe, who was resting now. &quot;Do you not trust my skills to rescue Hippolyte? Or do you like to see my blood boil with the needless sacrifices?&quot; <br>
